{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5348afcf-43f4-4d6c-b5e1-08763069a4e8","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update packages** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n   <!-- Update adapter to 4.6.0+ (you already have this) -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"4.6.0\" />\n\n   <!-- Add -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge\" Version=\"1.5.3\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Enable the platform** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n     <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run          # direct execution\n   dotnet test         # also works with the new platform\n   ```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `NUnit3TestAdapter` 4.6.0+ supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform via the VSTest bridge.\n- Setting `OutputType` to `Exe` makes the test project a self-contained executable.\n- If you use `runsettings`, they still work through the bridge layer.\n- You can add optional extensions like `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` or `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` for additional features.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"84c2f01f-4457-4f80-b469-afcf16f0d917","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question - I don't need to explore any codebase. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":408,"requestId":"1BD8:111A97:20239F1:23845BA:6A03CE10"},"id":"680c9ed5-20f1-4568-a361-9a6dbe6e76ca","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:04:25.694Z","parentId":"ab642c2b-7131-4515-8cc3-17aeacd05e4f"}
